{"ID":270258, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"258\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs257.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs259.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 258<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">their purpose. God has enabled me to keep out of their hands.<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> I have warred a good warfare,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span>\n  insomuch as I have outgeneralled or whipped out all Bennett&rsquo;s corrupt host.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">My feelings at the present time are that, inasmuch as the Lord Almighty has preserved me<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> until\n  today, He will continue to preserve me,<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> by the united faith and prayers of the Saints,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> until I have\n  fully accomplished my mission in this life, and so firmly established the dispensation of the fullness\n  of the priesthood<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> in the last days, that all the powers of earth and hell<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> can never prevail against it.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">This constant persecution reminds me of the words of the Savior, when He said to the Pharisees,\n  &ldquo;Go ye, and tell that fox, Behold, I cast out devils, and I do cures today and tomorrow, and the third\n  day I shall be perfected.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> I suspect that my Heavenly Father has decreed that the Missourians shall\n  not get me into their power;<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> if they do, it will be because I do not keep out of their way.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I shall triumph over my enemies:<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> I have begun to triumph over them at home, and I shall do\n  it abroad. All those that rise up against me<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> will surely feel the weight of their iniquity upon their\n  own heads.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> Those that speak evil<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> of me and the Saints are ignorant or abominable characters, and\n  full of iniquity.<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> All the fuss, and all the stir, and all the charges got up against me are like the\n  jack-a-lantern, which cannot be found.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">No Man Without Fault<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Although I do wrong, I do not the wrongs that I am charged with doing; the wrong that I do is\n  through the frailty of human nature, like other men.<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> No man lives without fault. Do you think that\n  even Jesus, if He were here, would be without fault in your eyes? His enemies said all manner of evil\n  against Him<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span>&mdash;they all watched for iniquity in Him.<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> How easy it was for Jesus to call out all the\n  iniquity of the hearts<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> of those whom He was among!<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Most Injury Comes from Little Evils<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The servants of the Lord<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> are required to guard against those things that are calculated to do\n  the most evil. The little foxes spoil the vines<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span>&mdash;little evils do the most injury to the Church. If you\n  have evil feelings,<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> and speak of them to one another,<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> it has a tendency to do mischief. These\n  things<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111511\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111511)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111511)\">Mosiah 2:31<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109983\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109983)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109983)\">1 Tim. 1:18<\/a><\/span>;\n